rComments: She was nice but the class was not enjoyable. Weekly quizzes took too much time to complete for being worth less than 2% each. Group work was not easy wih a course taught virtually. Class videos are way too long, boring, and ineffective at properly explaining concepts. Her instructions are VERY unclear! My entire team had to ask for clarification!

She seems to be an excellent teacher at first, but she is a tough grader. She knows her materials very well but doesn't mean that she is great at teaching. Try to avoid her classes because if you don't do well in her classes, she will suggest you to apply for college "easier" (She told me that, and I aced that same course with another professor)

Her expertise in STS is profound. She is a tough grader, but manageable if you put the work in. Visit her office hours, show that you are trying, work through your reasoning with her one on one. Seems great at first but never take a class with her, avoid it at all costs.
